column43: Comprehensive analysis of AML genomes has revealed co-occurring mutations in DNA and%0Ahistone modifying enzymes suggesting their crucial role in tumourigenesis. To gain inside into%0Athe role of those genes in AML we generated mouse models recapitulating mutations in part%0Aof the most frequent ones. We hypothesise that aberrant chromatin modification and%0Aunderlying effect on gene expression largely contribute to leukemogenesis. To test this%0Ahypothesis we propose to compare gene expression and DNA and histone modification in the%0Apresence or absence of single gene mutation in mouse hematopoietic stem and progenitor%0Acompartment in a pre-leukaemia setting. Characterisation of these models will inform the%0Abiology of AML%2C identify potential therapeutic targets and provide platforms for the%0Aassessment of novel therapeutics.%0A%0A%0AThis data is part of a pre-publication release.
